![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6a802b68-ec82-4bea-8d12-17a7fc97026a/Messenger_creation_685474327340099.jpeg?format=original)

The WWE has announced that Lex Luger will be joining the WWE Hall of Fame Class of 2025. This esteemed honor recognizes Luger's significant contributions to the world of professional wrestling.

Luger's illustrious career spanned over two decades, during which he competed in various promotions, including the National Wrestling Alliance (NWA), World Championship Wrestling (WCW), and the World Wrestling Federation (WWF), now known as WWE. He was a two-time WCW World Heavyweight Champion and held multiple other titles throughout his career.

The WWE Hall of Fame Class of 2025 is shaping up to be an impressive one, with Luger joining previously announced inductees:

Triple H, a 14-time world champion and one of the most influential figures in WWE history

Michelle McCool, a two-time Women's Champion and one of the pioneering female wrestlers of the 2000s

The WWE Hall of Fame induction ceremony is set to take place on the eve of WrestleMania 41, with further inductees expected to be announced in the coming weeks.

Lex Luger's induction is a testament to his enduring legacy and impact on the world of professional wrestling. Fans and fellow wrestlers alike will undoubtedly be celebrating this well-deserved recognition of his contributions to the sport.